    "#Q1. What are Eigenvalues and Eigenvectors? How are they related to the Eigen-Decomposition approach?\n",
    "#Explain with an example."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ef504016-16f9-475d-9774-f812092b22fd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Eigenvalues and eigenvectors are concepts in linear algebra that are used to analyze linear transformations. An eigenvector of a matrix A is a non-zero vector v such that when A is multiplied by v, the result is a scalar multiple of v. The scalar multiple is called an eigenvalue of A corresponding to v. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "df1bb547-3bc2-483f-99b3-a777932e83bc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Eigenvalues and eigenvectors are important because they help us understand how a linear transformation affects vectors in space."
   ]
  },
