    "#Q2. What is eigen decomposition and what is its significance in linear algebra?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "25daff53-ca4b-4dd3-95c6-e8515499e0fe",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Eigen decomposition is a method in linear algebra that decomposes a matrix into its eigenvalues and eigenvectors. It is also known as eigendecomposition or spectral decomposition\n",
    "\n",
    "The significance of eigen decomposition lies in its ability to simplify certain matrix operations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
