    "#Q5. How do you find the eigenvalues of a matrix and what do they represent?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "825a981b-98f1-4383-b000-a1abbad14ccd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To find the eigenvalues of a matrix, we need to follow these steps:\n",
    "\n",
    "Make sure that the given matrix A is a square matrix.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Subtract a scalar quantity λ from its main diagonal.\n",
    "\n",
    "Find the determinant of the resulting matrix and set it equal to zero.\n",
    "\n",
    "Solve for λ and the solutions are the eigenvalues \n",
    "\n",
    "Eigenvalues represent how much a matrix stretches or shrinks a vector. They are also used to determine whether a matrix is invertible or not"
   ]
  },
