    "#Q6. What are eigenvectors and how are they related to eigenvalues?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f8c939ec-e9e9-4e2e-8e26-ac7db9ffc460",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "An eigenvector of a matrix A is a nonzero vector v such that when A is multiplied by v, the result is a scalar multiple of v . In other words, Av = λv where λ is a scalar value known as the eigenvalue . Eigenvectors are important because they represent directions in which a linear transformation acts by simple scaling ."
   ]
  },
