    "Yes, a matrix can have more than one set of eigenvectors and eigenvalues . For example, consider a matrix A = [[1, 0], [0, 1]]. The eigenvectors of A are any nonzero vectors v = [x, y] such that Av = λv where λ is a scalar value known as the eigenvalue "
