    "#Q10. In what ways is the Eigen-Decomposition approach useful in data analysis and machine learning?\n",
    "#Discuss at least three specific applications or techniques that rely on Eigen-Decomposition."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a2e8a8a5-94ec-40bd-8844-0bf6ae7a60df",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "PCA is a statistical technique used to reduce the dimensionality of large datasets while retaining as much of the original information as possible . PCA uses Eigen-Decomposition to find the principal components of a dataset which are linear combinations of the original variables that capture the most variation in the data .\n",
    "\n",
    "Image Compression: Eigen-Decomposition can be used to compress images by representing them as a linear combination of their principal components . This reduces the size of an image while preserving its quality.\n",
    "\n",
    "Collaborative filtering is a technique used in recommendation systems to predict user preferences based on their past behavior and the behavior of similar users . Eigen-Decomposition can be used to factorize a user-item rating matrix into two matrices representing user and item factors respectively . This factorization can then be used to make recommendations for new items based on a user’s past behavior."
   ]
